<section class="section">
    <div class="r-container">
        <div class="d-flex flex-lg-row flex-column-reverse gap-3">
            <div class="col col-lg-12">
                <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                    
                    <p>
                        Our End of Life Care service offers gentle, compassionate support to individuals and families during the final stage of life. We understand the emotional weight that this period carries and approach every moment with respect, sensitivity, and dignity. Our focus is to ensure comfort, reduce distress, and create a peaceful environment where individuals can spend their final days in a place that feels familiar, safe, and meaningful.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        We work closely with the individual, their family, and health professionals to understand wishes, cultural needs, spiritual beliefs, and personal preferences. This helps us build a thoughtful and personalised plan that supports comfort, communication, and emotional wellbeing. Our carers assist with personal care, positioning, mouth care, and comfort routines, always ensuring privacy and dignity are maintained.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Symptom awareness forms a key part of End of Life Care. Although clinical decisions remain with nurses or doctors, our carers closely observe changes in condition and communicate promptly with professionals to ensure that discomfort is reduced and appropriate support is given. Calmness, patience, and presence are central to our approach, helping the individual feel safe and supported.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Families often experience emotional strain, uncertainty, and fatigue during this time. Our team offers guidance, encouragement, and a listening ear. We help families understand what to expect, provide practical support where needed, and enable them to spend meaningful time with their loved one rather than focusing solely on physical care.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        We believe that every person deserves dignity and compassion at the end of life. Our service aims to uphold comfort, maintain respect, and support peaceful moments for both the individual and those close to them. Through attentive and understanding care, we help families navigate this difficult journey with reassurance and emotional support.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
